Deliverables

The new GitHub App configured & installed. Submit app id, installation id, webhook secret, and location of private key (vault location).

A secure step-by-step script (or automation) that demonstrates how to produce an installation token and create the repository secret (Node or Python sample).

Final JSON summary and links to PR/merge.

If any permission problems occurred, create a GitHub Issue in the repo describing exactly which permission is missing and what admin action is required.

Security & governance

Do not commit secrets anywhere. Use repository secrets and vaults only.

If the token is compromised or exposed during the process, rotate it immediately and update the consumer application.

Do not rewrite main’s history (no force pushes) without explicit approval from org owners.

If you understand, execute these steps now and report progress after each major step. Do not attempt destructive operations (force-push, history rewrite) without explicit human approval.
